text: The Villager decided on the last second not to talk to you.
Hey there! Have you got $(red)4 iron ingots$() for me yet?
Thank you! Now I'll finally be able to make the armor for that guard... He wouldn't shut up about it! I don't have anything for you right now, but I swear I'll pay you back someday!
I need something! Can you help me fetch $(red)4 iron ingots$()? I'm running out of materials to make armor... I will repay you someday I promise!
Hello again! Have you fetched the paper for me yet? I want to draw you a map.

Here. There is a house infested by those sick and deluded hunters... One of my good friends have tracked down their location and marked it down in the map here. I'm sure they've been stocking up on loots they got from their enemies... Kill them and get their loot. If you could, look for a necklace they've stolen from me. They like to hide things under the table. See if you can find it, I'll do my best to repay you if you could ever return that necklace to me!
Come to think of it... There's a way for me to repay you. Can you fetch me a piece of paper so I can draw you a map?
Hey there. Did you find the pendant? They usually hide valuables under tables.
Finally, Juan... I got it back... I didn't break my vow... Oh, here ya go. Thank you for this, it means a lot to me.
Hey there Young Adventurer! Mind giving me a hand?
Well, do you have the rabbit foot?
Well great! I don't have much to pay for it... Please accept this cooked mutton, freshly cooked!
Good man! It's been a while since our hunters caught any rabbit... I would be grateful if you could spare me any $(red)rabbit foot$() you have.
Got time? Adventurer, can you fetch me something?
Learn How to Use the Cartography Table
Oh... hm, alright. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use it.
Don't get intimidated by the equipments on the table, you'll get the hang of it!
Hey there! Did you get the squid ink sac and paper I asked for? I only need 1 of each.
You're a life-saver! Here, explore and fill this map out.
Hello fellow, can you get me some squid ink and paper?
Did you get the $(red)5 rotten flesh$()?
Hey Adventurer, can you get me $(red)5 zombie flesh$()? I need it to prepare potions.
Great! Now my crops will grow faster than the other farmers'! Haha! Well thank you kind sir, here's an emerald.
My precious crops haven't been growing well these days... Do you think you can help me get $(red)8 bones$() so I can some fertilizers?
Greetings m'lord! Could you help me with something?
Ready to learn about fishing? Get me 15 emeralds!
Not that hard now is it? Don't swing around too much though, scares away the fish.
You want to learn about fishing? It takes patience, perseverance, and most importantly, a good teacher! I can teach you how to fish for 15 emeralds, what do you say?
10 Emeralds for learning how to use the fletching table, pretty cheap right?
Here you go. Have fun making arrows!
I'm teaching people how to use the fletching table for a mere 10 emerald. What do you say?
Huh? Oh you forgot. I was asking for $(red)4 Lion Hide$().
Thanks. Here, happy doing business with you.
I've heard good things about your work. I need you to collect some exotic goods, specifically: $(red)lion hide$(). I need 4 of those. Come back when you've got the goods.
Need your help collecting something, adventurer.
Please come back when you've gathered $(red)4 ink sacs$().

Many thanks. Unfortunately I found that our paper supply is also running low... Do you think you can help us get 10 pieces of paper for now> We'll restock soon, but we would really appreciate your help.
Could you help me retrieve 4 squid ink sacs?
Did you get the chance to gather the $(red)10 pieces of paper$()?
Thanks. I don't have emeralds to pay you at the moment... How's this for payment?
Greetings. I'd hate to bother you, but could you give me a hand with something?
What do you say? 10 Emeralds to learn how to use the stonecutter.
Wanna learn how to use the stonecutter? It'll be only 10 emeralds!
Give me 10 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use the loom!
Do you want to learn how to use the loom? I can teach you for 10 emeralds.
Please hurry up. I'm yearning for a $(red)bucket of milk$()!
Hey there! Could you fetch me a bucket of milk? I'm yearning for a taste.
Give me 10 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use the grindstone! Cheap right?
Do you want me to teach you how to use the grindstone? It'll cost 10 emeralds.
Oh? You've already defeated the eye holder before I gave you the map? Huh... Show me the exact eye the eye holder dropped then. As a matter of fact, drop it and pick it back up... Don't ask why!
I have no more information to give you my friend. Follow your calling.
Come back after you've fulfilled the requirements - $(red)Kill 10 pillagers$().
Here, use these to get your first upgrade from the $(green)goddess statues$()! I would recommend talking to some of the guards here if you want to learn some new skills. Good luck on your journey.
Ah... I don't think you'll be able to find the eyes in your current conditions. Come back to me once you've killed $(red)10 pillagers$(). I'll give you something to prepare you for your journey.
Thought you were an adventurer... Fine. Fetch me a piece of paper. I'll show you the whereabouts of the closest pillager camp we know of.
Here you go. You may find pillagers somewhere closer though. Those buggers are infested everywhere.
Good, seems like you're ready for an adventure! Ready to find your first eye?
See the map I gave you? Your first assignment is to exterminate the $(red)Goblin King$(). They can be found on top of their castles.
Good job. Seems you're ready to take on the $(red)Corrupted Ogre$(). Here, the creature dwelling in the marked spot is holding one of the eyes.
The Ogre is on a different level compared to the goblin king. Proceed with caution.

Well done. Perhaps you'll be able to face $(red)Knight Rober$() now. He is much weaker than who he once was, but I'd assume that he's still very dangerous, as he is still able to contain the power of the eye he's holding. Here's the map to his current whereabouts.

We have very little information on Knight Rober in his current state, but he should be quite weakened since the last war... Oh, remember to bring ender pearls. He has a nasty attack that can only be escaped via teleportation.

Wow, you've defeated Knight Rober huh. Was he tough? Back in the day he was one of the scariest opponent you could face in a duel, guess his age caught up to him finally. Well, the next eye-holder is another human. He's currently living peacefully in his farmhouse... Here's the map to his location.
Hm... the Nine Tails is not exactly a human. Oh well, you'll know when you see him.

Hmmph... At this point I'm not even surprised. Good job. The Nine Tails was a notoriously violent spirit... I have no idea why it decided to retire at an abandoned barn. Anyhow, here's the whereabouts of the next eye holder. Beware, this is nothing like the ones you've faced before.
The next eye holder is an undead. An undead with many tricks up its sleeves to be precise... It's surrounded by its followers, so you might have trouble getting to him.

The Skeleton Lord is probably the most powerful undead I've ever seen. I'm surprised you're able to take him down. Alright, let's see... The next eye is guarded by a renowned Holy Knight. I'm not sure if it's possible for even you. Anyhow, I'll give you its location. Proceed with caution.
The Sentinel Knight protected the Guardian Eye for centuries. None of the adventurers I know ever got past him... I heard that he's holding the key that frees the eye from its dormant state.

Amazing. Even the Sentinel Knight is no match for you... Well, you're approaching the end of your journey. How do you feel? ... Anyway, you'll need to summon the next eye holder. Here, take this knot of hair and the map to its summoning altar.

The fire giant had disappeared from our realm many moons ago. We were able to extract a knot of his hair before he left. The great clerics enchanted magic into the item, which should theoretically allow you to summon the giant should you offer the item at the altar. If you ever lose the hair knot, combine a fire charge with a basic fire resistance potion in a brewing stand to re-summon the item.
Well, I'm speechless... This is it adventurer. You have defeated all the eyeholders. If you have acquired 12 eyes already, look for the gateway into the End. God spede you.
I have no more information to give you my friend. Follow your calling.
The End... is just the Beginning??
So... you have defeated the dragon. I suppose that would make you the new ruler of the realm. Congratulations, brave conqueror. You have done... everything you could. Now, if you would excuse me.
The End... is just the Beginning??
The End... is just the Beginning??

If you must know... The deity who corrupted the ender dragon... He's still very much alive. But that being is simply too powerful, even for you. The map to reach him is held by the ender guardian. As for the whereabouts of the ender guardian... Our enderians may have a clue. I do not advise you to pursue this. You've done more than enough.
I.... I'm sorry I doubted you. You are, truly, one of a kind.                                      - End of Main Quest -
Welcome! Seems this is your first time visiting the guild. Would you like to take on your first quest?

To the best of my knowledge, there are currently 7 eyes that are unattended by eye holders. The ones that can be found in structures include the Cursed and the Old. As for the others... I think most of them can be crafted with the life forces in our realm, while a few of them may have been stolen by sentient beasts. The locals around may know more about that than I do. However, I do know that the clerics are currently in possession of the Evil Eye.
I think there's no need to look for the eyes anymore?
Did you get the $(red)5 Ender Pearls$() yet?
Adventurer, can you help me obtain 5 ender pearls?
Did you get the $(red)copper wrench and lever$()?
Hello there, I'm missing some parts to repair my machine. Can you get me $(red)a lever and a copper wrench$()?
Did you get the $(red)Soul Weed$() yet?
Can you get me $(red)1 Soul Weed$()? It can be found in the Nether Dimension.
Please get me a bow as soon as you can.
Thank you, now I can hunt again!
Can you make me $(red)a bow$()? Our weaponsmith is busy these days.
Could you fetch me a piece of paper? I'll draw you a map.
Here you go. Please tell it that I send my regards. I wouldn't be here without it.

I met a ghost when I was out mining... It was a horrible night with creatures spawning everywhere around me, but this kindred spirit protected me from every monster that came my way. Before I left for the village, the spirit told me to look for adventurers and bring them to him.
I have a strange tale to tell... would you hear me out, adventurer?
Fetch me a piece of paper? I'll draw you a map.
Here you go. Say hi to him for me.
An adventurer like yourself asked me for a favor a while ago. I couldn't really help him... But maybe you can. Bring me a piece of paper. I'll draw you a map to his location.
Hey. You're an adventurer, right? Got a minute?
Did you obtain a $(red)Heart of the Sea$() yet?
This looks... bizarre. But most things coming from the Ocean are of this nature... Anyway, thanks a lot adventurer. Here's your reward.

I need your help retrieving an item called $(red)Heart of the Sea$(). It can often be found in buried treasures, but I lack the experience and expertise an adventurer have to find it. Could you get it for me?
Hello adventurer. Could you get me something from the Ocean?
Did you get a piece of $(red)Mahogany Log$() yet?
Hey boy, can you get me a piece of $(red)Mahogamy Log$()?
I can teach you the skill - Emergency Escape. Just pay me 15 emeralds.
Hey young man, want to learn some combat skills?
Ah, almost forgot. Can you get me a piece of paper? I'll mark down the location of their hideout.
Here. Please hurry! We don't know what they're planning to do with the kid.
The pillagers have kidnapped a child from our village... Please go save him and bring him home. The guards here are swarmed with patrol duties, you're our only hope.
Please go save the child, and bring him back here.
You're a hero for what you did, adventurer. We will never forget what you've done for us. Here, I'll teach you a new combat skill - Death Harvest.
Got a side challenge for you: Defeat a Pillager Captain! Remember to drink milk before coming back... I'll kill you if you bring those pesky pillagers back to us!
Good job. Wait... You drank the milk right?
Adventurer! Our village requires your assistance!
Kill the Griffin, I'll pay you handsomely... But stay safe, please.
Oh thank the lords, you've returned! You took so long and the worst thoughts came to my mind... I'm glad you're okay. Here's your reward. Thanks again.

Have you ever come across creatures that are half-eagle, half-horse? They are called Griffins. These beasts have been pillaging my bee farms and terrifying my family. Can you help me exterminate the closest Griffin you can find around this village and bring me its feather? Don't worry, I'll pay you handsomely... I know how much risk you're taking to take on such a creature.
Adventurer... Interested in an extermination task?

Did you know? There are new faces in the dimension. Rumors have it that these man wear fabulous armor and unbreakable swords. I've had a chance to look at some of their armor design... Beautiful, but not practical. A decent hammer can smash through it with ease, haha!
Come here! Have a chat will ya?
Couldn't kill the $(red)5 Possessed Armor$() yet? Well, try harder, haha!
Haha, you actually did it! Mad man you are, but I like it! Here, take your reward, it's well-deserved!

Spirits manifest in the dimension in many forms. Sometimes they possess items, swords, and even armor! See if you can hunt down $(red)5 possessed... or hollow armor$(), whatever you wanna call it, and I'll give you a rewaard for your bravery. How does that sound?
Hey there boy! Up for a lil' challenge?
Oy, did you find the mystical biome $(red)Haze Mountain $() yet?
Is that so... That is quite disappointing to be honest. I thought there would be dragons residing in Haze Mountains... Oh well, at least now I know it's a myth. Thanks.

They say there is a biome within this dimension in which steams flow above boiling spring water and magical fog covers the entire mountain. Brave adventurer, if you ever come across such a place, please come back and let me know how it really is!
Oy! Got a favor to ask of you... Would you listen?
Did you make the $(red)Mushroom Stew$() yet?
Thank you! I just want to have a taste of a good bowl of $(red)mushroom stew$().
Oy! Could you cook something for me?
Hey. Have you crafted the blast furnace yet? Make sure to craft a new one instead of grabbing others!
Great! I can certainly make better equipments with this new facility. Thanks!
Thank you for listening. My blast furnace is breaking down... Can you $(red)craft$() a new one and give it to me?
Hey there! Ah hello stranger, could use your help with something!
Hey, u got the knife? Remember, it needs to be made with iron.
Nicely done! A fine knife it is, thanks.
Good man! Could you somehow get me an $(red)iron knife$()? Mine just broke...
Hey, can you help me out with something? It'll be quick.
You got the$(red) kangaroo meat and hide$()?

Ahh... so this is what kangaroo is like. A tender piece of meat indeed... The hide on the other hand isn't as good as the regular leather we use. A good trophy though... Thanks a lot adventurer. I don't have much to give you... Here, take these beef slices. The carcass just came in today so it's fresh!

Here in the village we usually only get the regular kinds of meat. I've heard that there are creatures called kangaroos that have tender and juicing meat on their tail. Could you get me a piece of their meat? And also I'd like to have a look at their hide as well.
Have you cooked the $(yellow)stuffed pumpkin$() yet? Don't worry I understand that it takes time!
That smells marvelous! Thank you so much, it will feed my family for days.
Hello kind sir. My spouse has been asking me to cook a dish called "$(yellow)stuffed pumpkin$()" and I'm too embarrassed to admit that I don't know how to make it... Can you cook one for me?
Have you got the $(red)5 deepslate stones$() yet? My blade's going dull.
Good work! As expected, these rocks contain both coarse and fine grit levels. Thanks a lot! Here, take it, it's your reward.

I'm looking for good sharpening stones for my knife. I've heard good things about a material underground called deepslate that's perfect for sharpening. Can you get me $(red)3 of those deepslate stones$()?
Remember, the Ash Barrens in the Nether. Come back to me after you visit there.
That is fascinating... Thank you for telling me about that place. Here's your reward. Well, off you go now... I've got an important decision to make.

Ah, back so early? Well, have you been to the nether? There is a biome called Ash Barrens in the Nether. See if you can find a castle there, even if you cannot, come back to me. I want to know what that place is like, please.
The $(light_blue)Chilling Sword$(). Let me know if you find it in the ash barrens castle.
So... he's really gone. Thank you, for bring me closure. Keep the sword. I don't have anything else to repay you.

Inquisitive are we? Well, the truth is... My brother was a wandering trader, a peculiar one. He enjoyed traversing through the Nether dimension... Even though he knew how dangerous it was. One day he left and... never returned. He left a note telling us he's going to a castle in the ash barrens. I was going to go there myself to find out if he's really dead or not, but I'm afraid I'll never return as well. After all, it's been months since his last departure, all I want is a proper closure... He had an artifact called $(light_blue)'Chilling Sword'$(). Do you think you can go to that castle and see if you can find this weapon?
You there! Give me a hand wou'cha?

Did you know that the cutting board can be used with a knife to cut down most food ingredients into smaller ingredients? It's worth experimenting a bit with not only food, but other resources such as logs or equipments!
Ey, got some tips for ya!
Oh... hm, alright. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use it.
Don't get intimidated by the equipments on the table, you'll get the hang of it!
Return to me when you finish travelling to these 3 biomes: Ancient Sand, Volcanic Peaks, White Mesa
Thank you for your detailed explanations. I think I will be able to draw them based on your description. Here, take your reward.

Basically, I need help figuring out what different biomes look like so I can draw them better on the maps. As an adventurer, I thought you perfect for the job! There are 3 biomes I'm currently interested in: The white cliffs, ancient sands, and the volcanic peaks.
Hello adventurer! I could use your help with something.
Oh... hm, alright. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use it.
Don't get intimidated by the equipments on the table, you'll get the hang of it!
Can you fetched me a piece of paper for me? I'll draw you a map.
Here, the group of foreign outlaws built a place where the marker is. Go and take out the leader.

I've heard information of a group of foreign outlaws from the east side that recently came and started pillaging villages. If you can fetched me a piece of paper for me, I can draw you a map to pinpoint their location for you.
Oh... hm, alright. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use it.
Don't get intimidated by the equipments on the table, you'll get the hang of it!
Come back when you've tamed an elephant... Actually, if.
Huh. You actually did it. Well, I heard these giant creatures love acacia blossoms. Here, don't ask why I've got them.
Did you know that there are these gigantic creatures called elephants residing in savanna biomes? Well, some of our kind managed to tame them. Think you can do it? Taming an elephant?
Oh well what have we here. Hope that task didn't give you any scar, haha! Here's your reward, I heard your kind likes diamonds.

Back for more, ey? Well, got another challenge for you, hunt down the reptilian beasts called crocodiles and bring me their scute. These creatures reside in swamp biomes. Be careful though, these creatures are ridiculously strong.
Hey adventurer! Got a challenge for you, up for it?
Oh... hm, alright. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use it.
Don't get intimidated by the equipments on the table, you'll get the hang of it!
Did you get the time to prepare the hamburger?
That is marvelous! I'll save it for later. Thanks a lot.
You look like a good cook. Could you cook something for me? There's a dish called $(red)Hamburger$(), do you know how to prepare that dish?
Oh... hm, alright. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use it.
Don't get intimidated by the equipments on the table, you'll get the hang of it!
It isn't that hard of a task is it? Craft a compass.
Good job. Run along now, did you expect a reward?
If you call yourself an adventurer, you gotta have a compass! Craft a $(red)compass$() and return to me.
10 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use the cartography table.
Don't get intimidated by the equipments on the table, you'll get the hang of it!
Hello my good sir. How would you like to learn to use the cartography table? It only costs 10 emeralds!
Forgot already? I need 5 spider eyes.
Hey there, could you help me get $(red)5 spider eyes$()?
Did yuo get the $(red)5 Blaze Rods$()? No worries, I know how hard it could be.
Well done. These materials are hard to come by here in the village. I'll use them sparingly. Thanks.
Hello there, could you help me get $(red)5 blaze rods$()? from the Nether dimension?
It seems you haven't finished your contract yet. Or did you forget what your contract was? Defeat $(red)2 silver beasts$().
You did well. I can feel the evil forces stopping their advances briefly. But their conquest is never ending, talk to me again if you wish for another contract.

There is a new type of evil manifesting in the dimension. These half man, half beasts are called $(red)silver beasts$(). You can find them wandering around at night. Exterminate 2 of these unholy creatures, and come back to me.
It seems you haven't finished your contract yet., or did you forget your assignment? Bring me $()5 orcs teeth$() as proof of your extermination task.
Well done. I have no more task for you at the moment. Just know that evil is always lurking about, stay vigilant.

Hello again, my next contract for you, is to exterminate orcs that roam around our land. These humanoid monsters have set up camps everywhere. I'm sure you've seen a few. Retrieve at least 6 orcs teeth and bring them to me as proof.
Greetings. I've got some extermination contracts for you, adventurer.
Nice, exactly what I needed. Thanks for your help!
Hello, can you help me get a $(red)ghast tear$()? I need it for my medical research.
I need your help retrieving a witch hat, any one would do. Witches seldom drop it.
YOU FOOL! NOW LETS BRING DOOM UPON THIS VILLAGE! I TAKE GLORY IN MY SACRIFICE IF IT MEANT BRINGING THIS VILLAGE TO ITS END!
Well, great job. You're such a hero. Is that what you wanted to hear?
Kill 3 regular village guards and come back to me. Don't let others see you. If your reputation gets too low I won't talk to you... For obvious reasons.
Hahaha... You vile man. Here, this is how you use it. Stay mischievous.

Still want something, 'hero'? Well, want to learn how to use the mixing cauldron? Kill 3 villager guards for me. I need their sacrifice for... Well it's none of your concern. Just kill 3. The quiet ones, don't choose the chatty ones that give you task. And do it quietly... if you can. I don't want to be linked with the murder.
Can you help me with something?
Ow! That's hot... Alright thanks for your help!
Hello, can you help me get a $(red)magma cream$()? I need it for my medical research.
Just a word of advice... Though most of the folks here are nice and all, some of them... not so much. Don't believe in everything people say, yea?
Hey young man, fancy a chat?
Many thanks, now I can grow a small pumpkin farm behind my house and begin my studies, haha!

As an ambitious farmer, my goal in life is to be an expert in growing different vegetations! However I've only had experience with wheat and potatoes... Would you help me find some pumpkin seeds? I will begin my ambitious conquest from there!
Hello good sir! Could you help me with something?
Forgot already? Don't worry let me remind you. I need a $(red)straw bale$().
A straw bale! Now we can make ourselves brand new straw hats! Thanks stranger.
Me and my frend's hats are a bit broken in. We wanna make a new hat you see... Could you get me a $(red)bale of straw$()?
Ey fella! Give me a hand would ya?
Good job, boy. Get me $(red)2 melon seeds$() as well?
Great, could you get me $(red)2 onions$()?
Did you get the $(red)2 melon seeds$()?
Get me 4 sweet berries as well? Villagers like myself can't risk going into the woods to collect these.   *You hear the villager chuckle as he finishes his sentence.*
So, did you get the $(red)4 sweet berries$()?
You've been great, young man. Do me another favor? I need 2 beetroots... I promise it's the last thing I'll ask.
Hello, did you get the$(red) 2 beetroots$()?
Well... Why are you still here? Are you expecting some kind of reward?
Well, how presumptuous of you. I didn't mention anything about a reward, did I? Run along now, boy, before I get the guards on you.
Hello young man, can you help me?

Oh you got it for us... I'm very grateful for that. I feel bad for asking for another favor... But do you think you can make $(red)2 loaves of bread$() for us? We're only good at growing and harvesting you see. You can use the wheat in our farm for that!
Our equipments are a bit broken in... do you think you can get us an $(red)iron hoe$()?
Let me know if you could make $(red)2 loaves of bread$() for us. No rush though!
Thanks a lot! Please accept this, it's not a lot but it's all I could afford at the moment.
Hey there, sorry to bother you! Could you help me get a few things?
Did you take the trip to Nether and retrieve the $(red)ghost pepper$() yet?
Ow, it's burning my hand! This is ghost pepper alright, haha! Here's your reward.

Spices seem to be the new craze in this village... I'm looking to grow the hottest pepper known and make a profit, haha! Have you heard of a kind of pepper called 'ghost pepper' that can be found the Nether? Well, I need you to collect $(red)3 of those ghost peppers$() and bring them to me.
Hey adventurer, you look like you've been through hell, haha! Just kidding, can you help me with something?
Yeah I can teach you how to fish, but it'll cost you 18 emeralds.
Not that hard now is it? Don't swing around too much though, scares away the fish.
Found any $(red)big guardians$()? If so give me their spike.
This is... extraordinary. The ocean is full of mystery... I've heard stories of giant squids as well, guess that would be true as well. Anyway, here's your reward. Thanks for that.

Great. Basically, an Oceanographer told me that there are these creatures out in the sea called guardians with spikes coming out of them... I find that hard to believe as I've never encountered anything like this for my whole life around the coastline. If you ever come across one and decide to kill it, could you give me one of their $(red)spikes$() as proof of their existence? I heard from the Oceanographer that only the big one drops its spike on death though.
Hello friend, can you help me figure something out?
Yeah I can teach you how to fish, but it'll cost you 18 emeralds.
Not that hard now is it? Don't swing around too much though, scares away the fish.
Thanks, I don't have much to give you. Um... take this cod, it's fresh.
My fishing rod is almost broken... can you make me a new one? The usual crafter is out of town these days...
Hello, can you help me out with something?
Yeah I can teach you how to fish, but it'll cost you 18 emeralds.
Not that hard now is it? Don't swing around too much though, scares away the fish.
(*You realize that that's not how sharks attack; And that only some of the most passive shark types such as $(red)Hammerhead Shark$() drop their teeth on death. But you decided to stay silent*)
Hahahaha.... I shall engrave my sister's name on this thing and wear it as a pendant. Thanks adventurer, here's your reward.

God bless you. Please help me hunt down those disgusting, vile creatures in the ocean. Biologists call them sharks. I call them the devils of the sea. Whilst at sea, I saw... I saw them tore my sister apart, limb by limb. Please help me take revenge, kill those nasty creatures and bring me back their tooth as a trophy.
Adventurer, please help me with something. I beg you.
Yeah I can teach you how to fish, but it'll cost you 18 emeralds.
Not that hard now is it? Don't swing around too much though, scares away the fish.
Did you get the hourglass? I don't even remember when I asked you to do it. God I need that thing. Please hurry.
Nice! Here's yo... wait, there's nothing inside. How do I use it? Hm... can you get me some $(red)redstone dust$()? So I can it in the hourglass.
I heard there are things that help you keep track of time. Those are called... what was it, oh right - $(red)Hourglass$()! Can you get me one of those?
Did you get the redstone dust? I think I just need 1.
It's so hard to keep track of time when I'm out fishing... Hey fella, can you help me out with something?
Yeah I can teach you how to fish, but it'll cost you 18 emeralds.
Not that hard now is it? Don't swing around too much though, scares away the fish.
Remember, the boat has to be made with the material $(red)Blighted Balsa$().
It's passable, could use a little more work. But this will do, thanks. Here's your reward, think you'll like it.

Great. Could you help me make a boat for fishing? Mahogany is usually the best kind of wood, but in the dimension we have the next best thing - $(red)Blighted Balsa$(). Make a boat with that and give it to me... I trust that as an adventurer you've had plenty of experience making one, right?
Know anything about boat making? Either way, wanna help me out?
Huh, alright. 15 Emeralds to learn how to use the fletching table.
Here you go. Have fun making arrows!
Thanks. Here, the arrows as promised.
I'm lacking some feathers for arrow making. Can you fetch me $(red)2 feathers$()? I can give you a few of the arrows after I've finished.
Hello, can you give me a hand?
Huh, alright. 15 Emeralds to learn how to use the fletching table.
Here you go. Have fun making arrows!
Did you get $(red)2 Roadrunner Feathers$() yet?
hm... The quality doesn't seem to be especially good. I'll see if I can make use of it in other ways. Anyway, here, for your trouble.
I heard that there is a type of terrestrial bird in desert biomes with excellent feathers for arrow making. Do you think you can hunt 2 of them down and bring me their drops?.
Huh, alright. 15 Emeralds to learn how to use the fletching table.
Here you go. Have fun making arrows!
Did you get $(red)the 4 spruce logs$() yet?
Good job. Here's an emerald for your work.
Did you know that spruce wood is the best for making the shaft of an arrow? Well doesn't matter either way. Could you get me some of those logs? I need at least 4.
Can you help me get something?
Huh, alright. 15 Emeralds to learn how to use the fletching table.
Here you go. Have fun making arrows!
Couldn't make the $(red)Slingshot$() yet huh? Well I get it... A good one is strangely difficult to make.
Yes, this is exactly what I have imagined it to be! Hm... It doesn't seem that impressive. Seems like it uses stones as ammo... Well, here you go, I don't really need it. Thanks for showing it to me!
That's right - Slingshot! I have been trying to get one working, but seems I lack the craftmanship needed to create a usable replica. Can you give it a try?
Primative villagers used to use something other than bows to hunt... Can you guess what that is?
Huh, alright. 15 Emeralds to learn how to use the fletching table.
Here you go. Have fun making arrows!
Forgot already? I was asking for $(red)12 Glowstone Dust$().
Thanks! Could you take these arrows as payment?
I'm trying to make tipped arrows. Can you get me a dozen glowstone dust?
Help a brother out will ya?
You got the goods yet? $(red)2 Black Bear Fur$().
Thanks. Here, pleasure doing business with you.
I need you to collect $(red)2 pieces of black bear fur$(). Come back when you've got the goods.
Got a job for you, adventurer.
You got the goods yet? $(red)2 White Bear Fur$() that is.
Thanks. Here, pleasure doing business with you.
I need you to collect $(red)2 pieces of white bear fur$(). They might be slightly tougher than other bear types, so be careful. Come back when you've got the goods.
Adventurer, got time for a job?
How goes the preparation of $(red)Honey Glaze Ham$()?
That is amazing, you do have a talent for cooking. Please accept these as gratitude.
Fantastic. Could you cook a dish called $(red)Honey Glaze Ham$()? Me and my friends are dying to taste this dish again.
Adventurer, you any good at cooking?
Thanks, these little guys are too fast for me to catch.
Could you fetch me a piece of rabbit hide?
Adventurer, got a small task for you, if you're ready.
Please get me a piece of paper so I can draw you a map.

Sorry for the trouble. Here is the place I want you to go. There is a book there that belonged to me. That place used to be a temple filled with scholars from all around the dimension, but I don't know how it is now. Please proceed with caution, and bring me my book.
Please return to me if you can find the book.
This book has... sentimental values. Words cannot express how grateful I am for your service. Here, take these. I've heard that adventurers use magic too, is that right?
Greetings. Would you be interested about going on an adventure for me, traveller?

In the annals of time, our world bore no arcane whispers until a power-thirsty sovereign altered fate. The Dead King, driven by insatiable ambition, devoted labor and wealth to unravel the mysteries of magic. His relentless pursuit birthed aberrant creatures, casting an ominous pall over our once tranquil realm. Whispers persist that even in death, his corpse became a conduit for the very forces he sought to command. Beware, brave one, for the shadows of his obsession linger. As you tread deeper, know this: The Dead King awaits, his lifeless shell now a vessel for magic's malevolence. Prepare for a confrontation like no other!
Greetings. Care to have a chat?
The 3 types of leaves to retrieve are: $(red)Dusk Leaves, Maple Leaves, Starlit Leaves$().
That is fascinating! How is it the case that there are common traits in plants that grow in completely different environments? Anyway, here's your reward.

Thanks for listening to my request. I've recently taken an interest in forestry, and thus I have been studying a lot about trees in our dimension; However it seems that there are other peculiar types of trees in other dimensions such as Everbright and Everdawn. Do you think you can help me gather a block of $(red)Dusk Leaves, Maple Leaves, and Starlight Leaves$() each for my research?
Hail! Did you go to the everbright or everdawn dimension yet? Either way, could you give me a hand?
Could I have 1 of your $(red)spirit orbs$()?
The structure of this is too complicated... Would you mind giving me another one of these?
I need another one of your $(red)spirit orbs$().
Haha... young man, you're too gullible. Don't place your trust in someone you've barely talked to. I'll return the orbs to you since I feel bad, but remember this: Not everyone is as nice as me.
Hello adventurer, can you help me with something?
Did you get your hands on an $(red)ancient debris$() yet?
This... this is amazing! Here, take my emeralds.
Could you get me an $(red)ancient debris$()? I've never had a chance to work with such high quality minerals... I am willing to pay a high price for it!
Learn How to Use the Stonecutter
hm.. alright. Give me 15 Emeralds if you want to learn how to use the stonecutter.
Got the $(red)lunar stone$() yet? You can find them in the Everdawn dimension.
Thanks. The quality is... subpar. I'll think of other uses for it.
Could you get me a $(red)lunar stone$() from the Everdawn dimension? I'm curious about its quality.
Learn How to Use the Stonecutter
hm.. alright. Give me 15 Emeralds if you want to learn how to use the stonecutter.
Got the $(red)turquoise stone$() yet? You can find them in the Everbright dimension.
hm... the quality is... not bad. I'll put it to good use, thanks!
Could you get me a $(red)turquoise stone$() from the Everbright dimension? I'm curious as to how it looks
Learn How to Use the Stonecutter
hm.. alright. Give me 15 Emeralds if you want to learn how to use the stonecutter.
When you get to the end, remember to bring me $(red)end stones$()
hm... the quality is... not bad. I'll put it to good use, thanks!
If you ever get to the end dimension. Could you get me an $(red)end stone$()?
Learn How to Use the Stonecutter
hm.. alright. Give me 15 Emeralds if you want to learn how to use the stonecutter.
No problem friend. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use the loom!
Please finish the extermination task as soon as possible. It's affecting my lambs.
Well-done. There's still a lot of them left, but I think I see less of them around now. Here's your reward.

Creepers are spawning more frequently around here at night... They don't harm us but they scare away our poor lambs. Can you exterminate them at night? I'll give you payments once you've reached 6 kills.
Would you be interested in an extermination task?
No problem friend. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use the loom!
Hello there, could you get me a pair of shears? Mine broke just now.
No problem friend. Give me 15 emeralds and I'll teach you how to use the loom!
Did you get the $(red)wheats$()? There should be enough in the farm.
Thanks. I don't have much to give you... would you accept these wool?
Hello, could you help me get 2 grown wheat from the farm for me? I need to it to breed my woollybacks.
Please get me a piece of $(red)paper$().
Here ya go, please return to me my beloved axe. It was my finest work yet.
Can you go to a place and retrieve an iron axe? The place was swarmed by orcs so I had to abandon it... Hold on, fetch me a piece of paper, I'll draw you a map.
Did you get me my iron axe yet? Please hurry.
YES! This is the axe I've made... I've never been able to top this, you know. Anyway, here's your reward. I appreciate your help.
Hey traveller, you seem to be good at retrieving things! Wanna help me out?
Hey there, I need a netherite ingot to make tools. Would you happen to have one that you can spare? I'll pay for it, of course.
Did you get the $(red)Crimson Wood Stem$()?
Thanks! I don't have emeralds at the moment... Will you take this diamond pickaxe? I just made it a few hours ago.
Hey there! Can you help me get some crimson wood stems from the Nether? I'm trying to make tools with special handles.
That's a rather unusual request... I'll charge ya 15 emeralds for that. Is that fine?
Did you get the $(red)16 iron ingots$()? Please hurry.

Thank you, I know that I shouldn't be asking an adventurer to help with resource gathering... But I don't have much choice. The pillager army is closing in, they're coming to this village soon... Let me know if you want an extermination contract, I'll be happy to offer.
Evil is coming. Can you help me get 16 iron ingot? I need to make more weapons for the guards... We're not prepared.
Please come back when you finished the extermination contract - $(red)Kill 5 Pillagers$().
Than- ... It seems the time has come. The pillagers are here. Comrade, I've forged this greatsword for times like this. Please put it into good use, and help us. All of our lives depend on you now.
Great. I need you to exterminate any pillager that you can find. We need to distract them so they won't have as much time planning their attack... Come back to me after you've killed 5.
Hey comrade. I need your help on something important.
That's a rather unusual request... I'll charge ya 15 emeralds for that. Is that fine?
Could you cook me a dish called "$(red)Pasta with Mutton Chop$()"?
mmhm! That looks amazing, I'll save it for later. Thanks.
Hey there, you look like you're a good cook. Could you cook something for me?
Could you fetch me a piece of paper? I'll draw you a map.
Please go to this location and try to... extract the gems from the creature. Bring me the gems please. I'll make sure that it'll be worth your while.

I've heard from the wandering travellers that they spotted a gigantic monster with gem spikes on its back a while ago. They say it was located in an area covered in obsidian spikes... I'm quite curious of the gems that this creature possesses. Could you fetch me a piece of paper? I'll show you where it is.
Did you get the  $(red)gem$()? You might have to exterminate the creature to get it.
Wow... this is amazing. This is simply... astonishing. I will need some time with this. Can you bring me a wooden stick? I Think I might be able to make you something special.
Still working on it! Did you get the stick yet?
Here you go. This might be my best work so far, heh.
Hey Adventurer. Could you investigate something for me?
That's a rather unusual request... I'll charge ya 15 emeralds for that. Is that fine?
That is the best honey I've drank in a while! Thanks!
I'm dying to drink a bottle of honey! Could you fetch one for me?
Please let me take a look once you've obtained the $(red)dragon egg$(), it has always been my dream to see one.
So this is how it looks like... Did you know that you can place the dragon egg and it'll hatch a new dragon? Here, I'll teach you how to tame it: Just feed it as much fish as you can... Simple right?
Great! Did you know that upon defeat, the Ender Dragon will drop its egg? I was wondering if it would be possible for you to let me take a look at the $(red)dragon egg$(), it will make my day.
Hello adventurer... When you defeat the enderdragon, could you do something for me?
Please let me take a look once you've obtained the $(red)dragon egg$().
Sorry to do this to you, my friend... But I need it. Goodbye.
Great! Did you know that upon defeat, the Ender Dragon will drop its egg? Basically, I would like you to let me take a look at the $(red)dragon egg$(), could you do that for me?
Hello adventurer... When you defeat the enderdragon, could you do something for me? Just a small thing.

There's a hidden creature living in the depths of the end dimension - The Void Worm. You can summon it by throwing the larva into the depths of the end. The larva can be created by throwing crimson mosquito larva into enderiophage's capsid.
Hello adventurer, care to have a chat?
Come back to me once you've made the dish $(red)Ennegel Pasta$(). I'll pay you handsomely for it.

This flavor...! Just like my ma's cooking... Thank you adventurer, you have no idea how grateful I am for this. Here, take this. It's a katana forged with ender power. I doubt there's a weapon out there stronger than this one.
There's a dish called Ennegel Pasta. It's a dish that can only be made with ingredients found in the End Dimension... Please gather all the resources and cook one for me.
Hello adventurer, there's a dish that I think only you can make for me. I'll pay handsomely for it, what do you say?
Did you get the $(red)10 Redstone Dust$()
Can you give me $(red)10 Redstone Dust$()? I'll pay for it of course.

I'm sorry for the vague description... But the issue is I don't know where the structure is or what it looks like. It's a villager castle with create contraption, I believe you'll know it when you see it.
That is fascinating! However, I do not think these villagers built it themselves, they don't have an engineer with them... Someone is keeping them there. Either way, thanks a lot. Here's a cookie.
I've heard that some of our kind have moved away to individual castles with Create Contraptions.. If you ever come across one, could you tell me how the place is like?
Did you defeat the land golem and obtain his $(red)Golem Eye$() yet?

By the Heavens! This is one of the most fascinating item I've ever seen. It's more than I've ever imagined. Here, take these redstones as payment. I'm sorry but I don't have emeralds on me at the moment.

Thanks for listening to my request. Are you aware of the 'battle towers' in this dimension? They're everywhere around the world. I am particularly interested in the Land Towers, and the golem residing inside. The eye that the guardian drops hold tremendous kinetic energy... Do you think you can help me get one for my research?
Hello adventurer, can you help me with something?
Did you get the $(red)Anemone Rose Bulb$() yet?
Can you give me $(red)1 Rose Bulb Anemone$() if you come across any?
Did you get the $(red)Spore Blossom$() yet?
Can you give me $(red)1 Spore Blossom$() if you come across any?
Can you give me $(red)1 Rafflesia$() if you come across any?
Did you get the $(red)Orange Ball Cactus$() yet?
Can you give me $(red)1 Orange Ball Cactus$() if you come across any?
Did you get the 2 patches of $(red)Hemlock$()?
Thanks. Now I can make the lure.
Great! I need $(red)2 Patches of Hemlock$(). It's too toxic for most animals, but not for the vile beast that I'm hunting...
Can you help me gather ingredients for animal lure?
Did you get $(red)16 arrows$() from the fletcher? I'll pay you back for it.
Thanks, you're a life saver! I'm not good with the local fletcher so it was a bit awkward to ask...
Hey there, can you get $(red)16 arrows$() from the local fletcher? I'll pay you back for it.
Did you get a piece of $(red)Frostbright Log$() yet?
Hey boy, can you get me a piece of $(red)Frostbright Log$()? It can be found in the Everbright dimension.
I need an $(red)Iron Axe$() to work!
My friend, can you help me get a new axe from the toolsmith? I'll pay you back I promise!
Did you get a piece of $(red)Dusk Log$() yet?
Hey boy, can you get me a piece of $(red)Dusk Log$()? It can be found in the Everdawn dimension.
I can teach you the skill - Vampirize for 15 emeralds.
Hello adventurer, want to learn a combat skill?
If you're ready to save the kid. Give me a piece of paper, I'll draw you a map.
The scoundrel have set up base here. The kid must be still with them... Please hurry. Bring him back to us!

The pillagers who've set up base near our village took away a child... The number of guards in this village are not strong enough to rush in and save the child. If you can help, please fetch me a piece of paper. I'll show you where they are.
Save the child, please. Bring him home.
Amazing! You've actually did it! To be honest I wasn't optimistic about the kid's survival... Here, I'll teach you a new skill - Meteor Slam. It's the only way I could repay you.
Please help us adventurer... You're our only help left!
Brave man. Please give me a piece of paper so I can show you where the creature is at.
Here, the cleric is the one who provided us with this information though. So I'm not sure if it's completely accurate. Either way, find this creature, kill it, and bring back whatever it drops.

There is a $(red)Cave Dweller$() residing in a cave near us. This creature is extremely dangerous... Our clerics think that it will one day come up from below and slaughter us all... Can you exterminate this creature and bring me $(red)parts of his remain$() as proof?
Did you exterminate the cave dweller yet? If so bring me its drops.
It's strange to imagine a creature with natural armor this tough... Well, I'm glad its dead. Here, I'll teach you a new skill as payment - Dual GreatSword.
Adventurer! I have an extermination task for you.
Bring me a piece of paper, I'll show you where it is on the paper.
Here, it's rather easy to spot once you get close. Good luck, and bring me whatever it drops.

There is a man-eating $(red)Giant$() living near us. Some of our villagers and guards have already been killed by him. The guards, including me, are too intimidated by its sheer size. But as far as we know, it's not too strong or intelligent. I believe you'll be able to take him on.
Did you exterminate the giant yet? If so bring me its drops.
Good job! This is one of its eye alright... Let's see, I'll teach you the combat skill - Demolition Leap, as payment. This skill greatly improves your agility during combat!
Adventurer! Interested in an extermination task?
Could you fetch me a piece of paper? I'll draw you a map.
Thanks. The creature dwells around this area. Take care.

Thanks a lot... I was on a trip with my family, until we came across this... wolf. But it didn't act like one. If anything it behaved more like... a man. It ran to us as soon as it laid eyes on us, and.. well, I'm the only one who made it out alive. That was 2 years ago, but I still remember the place where it happened. Please, exterminate this creature. Avenge my family.
Did you do it? Did you kill the $(red)half wolf?$()
Thanks. I'll take your word for it. I'm glad to know that no one else will fall victim to these horrible monsters from now on.
Hey Adventurer. Would you mind hearing me out?
Forgot already? Defeat the Ghost of Captain Cornelia with your melee. Then come to me to claim your reward.
Mad man! You've actually done it! Here, take your reward. Heard you guys like diamonds right? Take some!
Hello brave traveler. Up for a challenge?
6 Emeralds if you want me to show you where the Monstrosity is in the Nether Dimension.
Here you go, happy hunting! Remember, this map will only work if you open it in the Nether. Sure is confusing, ey?
When I was in the Nether Dimension, I found a peculiar structure with a monstrous golem dwelling inside. I'll show you where it is on the map if you give me 6 emeralds.
Hey fellow adventurer! I got an offer for you.
4 Emeralds, and I'll show you where you can find the materials needed to summon Ignis.
Here it is. Don't summon that abomination near this village. And remember, this map will only work if you open it in the Nether. Don't ask me why... I have no clue.

Did you hear about a legendary being - Ignis? I heard that it's ever stronger than... the Fire Giant. If you want to summon it, you'll need to obtain certain materials in the Nether Dimension. I can show you where these materials can be found... for a price. 4 Emeralds to be exact.
Interested in an offer, young man?
15 Emeralds, and I'll teach you how to use the skill Step.
Here you go. I prefer using this to rolling around in the mud!
I got an interesting skill I can teach you - Step. That'll cost you 15 Emeralds though.
Don't ask me why. It's none of your concern, kiddo. Just get me the $(red)Fire Dragon Heart$().
Knew I could count on ya. Here ya go.
I'll be off in the mines in a bit... Got time to chat?
I've seen these ice dragons once. Terrifying beings... Yet their essences are so majestically alluring. I must investigate the elements within it.
Splendid! Here are your rewards. I must now begin my research.
The map to the summoning podium will cost you 5 emeralds.
Nice doing business with you, friend.
I know of a place where adventurers go to to summon powerful being. Would you like to know where?
Nothing is free my friend. Give me 5 emeralds and I'll give you the direction to the Ender Guardian.
Very good, here you go. Remember, don't open this map until you're actually in the End. Don't say I didn't warn you.
The Ender Guardian guards a very important item. Would you like to know where it is?
Did you know? The FrostMaw snatched the Cold Eye away from the Yeti guarding it! I've heard this story from a couple travelers already, so it must be true... What a chaotic world we live in.
Hey there, have time for a chat? I reckon it'll be worth your while.
Oh you're back! Did you get the $(red)Sculk Sensors$() yet?

This... looks so bizarre. Did you run into the Warden? Well, I'm guessing that you didn't, seeing as you're still alive. Anyway, here's your reward. This item should keep you safe from the mundane slimes.
Did you receive the blessing of the Orca already?
Interesting... so that's how it's done. You're a fascinating fellow. I'm glad I ran into you! Now I must go... God spede you.

Finally, someone to talk to! Let me tell you something: There is a giant Rootless Floating Palace somewhere in this realm. Few people know about it, let alone its whereabouts... and lucky for you, I happen to be the on in a million. I'll tell you what. If you ever get the chance to be blessed by an Orca, let me know exactly how it happened, and how it made you feel. Do that, and I'll tell you where the palace is, for free! A powerful sorcerer resides in that palace, and concealed its treasure deep within the core within. As an adventurer, this must sound enticing to you ey?
My fellow. This place is boring me to death... Up for a little chat? It'll be worth your while.
I can teach you the skill - Vengeful Parry for 15 emeralds.
Got a skill to teach you, but for 15 emeralds!
I can teach you the skill - Mindset for 15 emeralds.
Adventurer! I can teach you a combat skill for 15 emeralds!
I can teach you the skill - Pain Anticipation for 15 emeralds.
Here you go. Take the pain!
How you doing? Want to learn a skill for 15 emeralds?
I can teach you the skill - Rain Cutter for 25 emeralds.
Do you want to learn a skill for 25 emeralds?
I can teach you the skill - Critical Knowledge for 15 emeralds.
Hey there. Do you want to learn a skill for 15 emeralds?
I can teach you the skill - Stamina Pillager for 18 emeralds.
Have fun pillaging! But not too much fun.
Hey there. Do you want to learn a skill for 18 emeralds?
I can teach you the skill - Revelation for 20 emeralds.
Here you go. Get some pratice in before using it in combat!
You want to learn a skill? Okay, that will set you back 20 emeralds.
So I can teach you the skill - Forbidden Strength for 13 emeralds... What do you say?
Here you go. Be careful using this skill!
Hello! I can teach you a skill for 13 emeralds.
So I can teach you the skill - Parrying for 20 emeralds... What do you say?
Hello! I can teach you a skill for 20 emeralds.
So I can teach you the skill - Swordmaster for 15 emeralds... What do you say?
Hello! I can teach you a skill for 15 emeralds.
I can teach you the skill - Phanthom Ascent for 25 emeralds. Pretty good deal if I do say so myself!
Here you go adventurer! Just jump twice to use the skill.
Oh hello, want to learn a new combat skill?
I can teach you the skill - Technician for 15 emeralds.
I know the skill - Hypervitality. I can teach you that for 20 emeralds.
The book should provide you with the secrets of this art.
Hey there. Want to learn a passive combat skill?
I can teach you the skill Precise Roll for 18 emeralds.
Hey there, I can teach you a combat skill if you'd like... For a price of course.
So? I can teach you the skill Impact Guard for 15 emeralds. What do you say?
There ya go! Run along now!
I'm busy... What do you want? Oh... for a combat skill?
I can teach you the dodge roll for 15 emeralds. What do you say?
There ya go! Run along now!
I can teach you how to do a simple dodge roll, in case you don't know how to do so already...
I can teach you the skill - Endurance for 15 emeralds. What do you say?
I can teach you a combat skill if you'd like.
I can teach you the skill - Conqueror Haki for 30 emeralds. What do you say?
Here you go. Be careful using this skill among allies.
I can teach you a very powerful combat skill for a price...
I can teach you the skill - Dodge Master for 15 emeralds. What do you say?
Here you go. This is one of the hardest skills to use, yet highly effective with proper execution.
I can teach an expert skill for a low price. What do you say?
I can teach you the skill - Heart Shield for 15 emerald blocks. What do you say?
Hello there good sir. May I interest you in a trade?
I can teach you the skill - Bull Charge for 30 emeralds. What do you say?
Here you go. Don't go running off a cliff, mind you.
I can teach you the skill - Shadow Step for 25 emeralds. What do you say?
I know a combat skill that you might be interested... What do you say?
I can teach you the skill - Perfect Bulwark for 15 emeralds. What do you say?
Want to learn a special skill?
I can teach you the skill - Counter Attack for 20 emeralds. What do you say?
Want to learn a special skill?
I can teach you the skill - Ender Step for 30 emeralds. What do you say?
This is the skill passed down from the legendary beings - The Twins. You can find them in the end, or so I've heard...
Want to learn something? I'm probably the only one around that can teach you this particular skill.
I can teach you the skill - Meditation for 15 emeralds. What do you say?
Now water can flow, or it can crash... Be water my friend.
I can teach you the skill - Arrow Tenacity for 15 emeralds. How about that?
Hey, I can teach you something.
I can teach you the skill - Dancing Edge for 20 emeralds. Trust me, it's worth the price!
Great choice! Good luck on your journey.
Hey, heard you're looking for new combat skills to learn. I think I've got just what you need.
Alright, so I can teach you the skill - Ender Obscuris for 20 emeralds. You good for it?
There you go. Don't use it to scare the villagers around, mind you!
If you want to learn how to surprise your enemy, I've got just the trick...
I can teach you the skill - Adrenaline for 15 emeralds. What do you think?
Oh hello, I can teach you a simple but useful skill!
I can teach you the skill - Guard for 20 emeralds. What do you think?
Oh hello, I can teach you a simple yet powerful skill!
I want you to complete 2 tasks: Receive a blessing from the noble sunbird, and to summon a mutant snow golem. Then I shall consider handing you Agony.
Remarkable! Take it. Its former bearer fell to ferocious beasts. May your fate diverge from his.
In my grasp lies the fabled blade - Agony. Yet, to wield its might, you must demonstrate your worthiness to me.

Two tasks lie before you: Kill any creature from 100 blocks away with an eagle wearing a hood, and feed a pig a fermented spider eye then throw Chemical X at it. Fulfill them, and I shall contemplate entrusting you with Torment.
Well done! Here it is. Its former master was a fearsome piglin warrior.
I wield the legendary blade - Torment. Yet, to earn its allegiance, you must demonstrate your valor and worthiness.

Complete two tasks as I demand, and only then shall I consider bestowing upon you the mighty Ruine. Receive a Tiger's Blessing after feeding it meats, and loot a Nether Reactor in Nether's toxic heap.
Excellent work! Here it is. Much knowledge is sealed within the blade's edge...
possess the legendary blade - Ruine. Yet, to deem you deserving, you must prove your mettle and worthiness.

Before I entrust you with the ender blasters, you must accomplish two tasks to prove your worth: Extinguish a Pipelin Sentry from Nether's infernal dunes, and shear a fully mature mushroom colony. Keep in mind that you will need to develop rich soil in order to achieve that.
